---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ProsePage from '../components/ProsePage.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About BMI Result — Free BMI Calculator Tool"
  description="BMI Result is a free, ad-supported BMI calculator built for fast, accurate body mass index calculation in metric and imperial. Learn about our team and methodology."
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "AboutPage",
      "name": "About BMI Result",
      "url": "https://bmiresult.com/about/",
      "mainEntity": {
        "@type": "Organization",
        "@id": "https://bmiresult.com/#org",
        "name": "BMI Result",
        "url": "https://bmiresult.com/",
        "logo": "https://bmiresult.com/favicon.svg",
        "description": "BMI Result provides free, instant BMI calculation tools with educational health content based on WHO and CDC guidelines."
      }
    })} />
  </Fragment>

  <ProsePage title="About BMI Result" lead="We help people understand their body mass index with a fast, honest, mobile-first calculator.">
    <p>
      BMI Result (bmiresult.com) is an independent health utility site. We are not a
      hospital, insurer, or government agency. Our goal is to provide a better user experience than legacy
      calculator pages: instant BMI results, accessible design, dark mode, and clear educational content.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink) mt-8">Our methodology</h2>
    <p>
      All BMI calculations use the standard formula recommended by the
      <a href="https://www.who.int/news-room/fact-sheets/detail/obesity-and-overweight" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-(--color-link) hover:underline">World Health Organization (WHO)</a>:
      <strong>BMI = weight (kg) ÷ height² (m)</strong>. Adult BMI categories follow the WHO classification
      (underweight &lt;18.5, normal 18.5–24.9, overweight 25–29.9, obese ≥30). For children and teens,
      we use age- and sex-specific percentile charts based on
      <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/growthcharts/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-(--color-link) hover:underline">CDC growth chart data</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink) mt-8">Content standards</h2>
    <p>
      Health content on this site is written for general educational purposes and is based on peer-reviewed
      research and official guidelines from the WHO, CDC, and NHLBI. We clearly state the
      <a href="/" class="text-(--color-link) hover:underline">known limitations of BMI</a> — including
      its inability to distinguish muscle from fat, ethnic variation in risk thresholds, and unsuitability
      during pregnancy. We encourage all users to consult a qualified healthcare professional for
      personal health decisions.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink) mt-8">Editorial independence</h2>
    <p>
      BMI Result is funded by advertising. Advertisers have no influence over our calculations, content,
      or health recommendations. We do not sell user data.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink) mt-8">Who we serve</h2>
    <p>
      Content on this site is written for adults in the United States and internationally who search for
      "BMI calculator" and related terms. We support English, Hindi, Spanish, and French.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-6">
      Questions? Visit our <a href="/contact/" class="text-(--color-link) hover:underline">contact page</a>.
    </p>
  </ProsePage>
</BaseLayout>